# Approach
1. Create a Stack of String with following condition.
2. Iterate the loop till you doesn't reaches the end of string.
3. If you encounter a "/" then ignore it.
4. Create a temp String & Iterate the while loop till you doesn't find "/" and append it to temp.
4. Now check if temp == "." , then ignore it.
5. If temp == ".." then pop the element from the stack if it exists.
6. If no of the above 2 matches push temp to stack as you find a valid path.
7. Check out temp string on basis of above conditions till you doesn't find "/".
8. Now add all stack elements to result as res = "/" + st.top() + res
9. If res.size() is 0 then return "/" if no directory or file is present.
At last return res.
```
