![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/3baa5c6a-2f08-4b42-b5cd-5cb6cfe3babb_1645511943.7372382.png)

Here we are given to encode the column title string into a numeric value
A-Z we know mapped as 1-26 which we can get as 
columntitle[i]-'A'+1 given all uppercase letters

Now if we observe carefully
if length of this input string is 1 its eazy we can directly say 1-26 whatever it is
Now look at this string for example:
AAB
lets break it into a part and try to visualize it
(A ->(  A->  (B)  ))

Now B is 2 we know.
Going till Z we will have 26 then again a series starts like AA-AZ which goes from 27-52
so now as we move our pointer to the 2nd last character as we are moving right to left
we see what character it is,  for our case its an 'A' but in the 2nd last place so it should start from 26+(whatever we have accumulated after it)
if the 2nd last character was a B instead, (after AZ we start with BA-> which is 53 which means 26*(2)+1)

and similarly in the 3rd character we have 26 x 26 x (whatever the character is)

So our eg string AAB can be encoded as
(26 x 26 x 1) +(26 x 1)+(2)
......................................... _______
.............................................. B
........................___________
________________A
A
------
