solutions.content:
Since the numbers are integer we just need to check 32 bits. We will one by one get the bits starting from the rightmost bit and check if we need to set that bit or not and then calculate the carry.

e.g. 
0 0 1 1
0 0 0 1

i = 0,  a1 = 1, b1 = 1 and carry = 0 initially
Since both a1 and b1 are 1 we will get 0 bit in that position as (1 + 1) will give 0 with carry 1.
We will add this bit to the sum along with previous carry.
So, the following operation will help us to check that if the resulting bit will be 0 or 1. We just need to remember the basic bit operations :

0 + 0 = 0
0 + 1 = 1
1 + 1 = 0  and carry 1
1 + 1 + 1(carry) = 1(bit will again set to 1) and carry = 1

`sum |= a1 ^ b1 ^ carry`

Then we will calculate the carry for next position bits by checking if any of the two (a1, b1, carry) is 1 making the carry as 1 else 0. 

for i = 0, 
sum = 0 0 0 0
carry = 1

We will repeat these steps for every bit position.

For i = 1, a1 = 1, b1 = 0, carry = 1
So, we will get a 0 again for this bit position as a1 and carry are 1

So, for i = 1
sum = 0 0 0 0
carry = 1

For i = 2, a1 and b1 will be 0 as no set bits left and carry = 1 from previous bit operation
sum = 0 1 0 0
carry = 0

The remaining iterations will not do anything as all the bits and carry are now 0.

```
class Solution {
    public int getSum(int a, int b) {
        int sum = 0, carry = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) {
            int a1 = a & (1 << i);
            int b1 = b & (1 << i);
            sum |= a1 ^ b1 ^ carry;
            carry = ((a1 & b1) | (b1 & carry) | (a1 & carry)) << 1;
        }

        return sum;
    }
}
```

