solutions.content:
To count the projection area onto xy-plane, we simply count the number of cells in the matrix with value greater than 0 and add 1 for to the result for each such cell (since all cubes are 1 by 1).

To count the projection area onto xz plane, we find the maximum value in EACH ROW and add that maximum to total area.

To count the projection area onto yz plane, we find the maximum value in EACH COLUMN and add that maximum to total area.

```
class Solution {
    public int projectionArea(int[][] grid) {
        int xy = 0, yz = 0, xz = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < grid.length; i ++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < grid[0].length; j ++) {
                if(grid[i][j] > 0)
                    xy ++ ;
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < grid.length; i ++) {
            int max = 0;
            for(int j = 0; j < grid[0].length; j ++) 
                max = Math.max(max, grid[i][j]);
            xz += max;
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < grid[0].length; i ++) {
            int max = 0;
            for(int j = 0; j < grid.length; j ++) 
                max = Math.max(max, grid[j][i]);
            yz += max;
        }
        return xy + xz + yz;
    }
}
```

