Something to keep in mind with this problem is that only the max heights matter for each row and column.
If we shine a light perpendicular to the X-axis only the shadows of the tallest cubes will cast shadows.
Similarly, if we shine a light perpendicular to the Y-axis only the tallest cubes cast shadows.
Lastly, the XY direction is the area of the grid minus the number of buildings with zero height.
