# Description
In top projection, number of cubes will be `n^2`, but in case of `0` values there will not be any cube and we should not count it.

In case of front and side projections it will be the sum of maximum values in the rows and columns of matrix.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n^2)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {

    public int projectionArea(int[][] grid) {
        int n = grid.length;
        int sum = n * n;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int rowMax = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
            int colMax = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                rowMax = Math.max(rowMax, grid[i][j]);
                colMax = Math.max(colMax, grid[j][i]);

