# Intuition of this Problem:
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
**NOTE - PLEASE READ APPROACH FIRST THEN SEE THE CODE. YOU WILL DEFINITELY UNDERSTAND THE CODE LINE BY LINE AFTER SEEING THE APPROACH.**

# Approach for this Problem:
1. Initialize an empty vector "ans" to store the final result
2. Initialize "carry" to 0 and "i" to the index of the last digit of "num"
3. Loop while there is a digit left in k, or there are digits left in num, or there is a carry value.
4. Compute the sum by adding the carry, the last digit of k (if k has digits left) and the i-th digit of num (if num has digits left).
5. Compute the carry by taking the sum divided by 10.
6. Add the digit to the front of the "ans" vector by taking the sum modulo 10.
7. Decrement i and divide k by 10 (if applicable).
