My solution to [67. Add Binary](https://leetcode.com/problems/add-binary/)  => [https://leetcode.com/problems/add-binary/solutions/3186596/have-you-thought-this-way-beats-100-self-explanatory-code/](https://leetcode.com/problems/add-binary/solutions/3186596/have-you-thought-this-way-beats-100-self-explanatory-code/)

![3549-pepepopcorn.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ae3f7606-e894-4cd9-8ec8-79ed937375ed_1676439722.7051065.png)

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
As you have learned basic summation by hand. You probably have an idea about the **carry**. In this solution we will also need to keep and store **carry** in a variable. You probably start from the right then calculate to the left.

Let's see for an example:
```
num = [2,1,5], k = 806
```

| carry | num1 from k | num2 from num[] | sum | add to list | updated carry |
|-------|------|------|-----|-----|-----|
|0 | 6 | 5 | 11 | 1 | 1 |
|1 | 0 | 1 | 2 | 2 | 0 |
|0 | 8 | 2 | 10 | 0 | 1 |
|1 | 0 | 0 | 1 | 1 | 0 |

To find the last digit from k, we will do k%10. As this is a 10 base number, we need to mod 10. If this was 2 base (binary) or 8 base (octal) number then we need to do k%2 or k%8 respectively.
After doing that, we update k by doing k/10. This means we are erasing the last digit. Again, as it is 10 base number we are using 10. For 2 or 8 base number we will use 2 or 8.

We iterate the loop of the array. After the iteration is complete, we check if k is 0. If it is not, we further add the values from k.

Lastly, an important part is, whether carry is 0 or not. If it is not 0, we must add that to the list.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
We are declaring another list to store the output.
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code [Java]
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        List<Integer> list = new LinkedList<>();
        int carry = 0;
        for(int i=num.length-1; i>=0; i--){
            int num1 = 0;
            if(k!=0){
                num1 = k%10;
                k/=10;
            }
            int num2 = num[i];
            int sum = carry + num1 + num2;
            carry = sum/10;
            list.add(sum%10);
        }
        while(k!=0){
            int sum = carry + k%10;
            k/=10;
            carry = sum/10;
            list.add(sum%10);
        }
        if(carry!=0){
            list.add(carry);
        }
        Collections.reverse(list);
        return list;
    }
}
```

