# Implementation
* Time complexity: O(N) where N is the length of A.
  Traversing the input array takes O(N). List.Add() is a O(1) operation. List.Reverse() is a O(N) operation. 

* Space complexity: O(N)
```
public class Solution {
    public IList<int> AddToArrayForm(int[] A, int K) {

        int carry = K, i = A.Length - 1;

        List<int> res = new List<int>();
        while(i >= 0 || carry > 0)
        {
            int val = i >= 0? A[i] : 0;
            int sum = val + carry;
            carry = sum / 10;
            res.Add(sum % 10);
            i--;
        }

        res.Reverse();
        return res;
    }
}
```

# Some thoughts
Using List.Insert() to build result from LSD (least significant digit)to MSD (most significant digit) will save a Reverse. However, List.Insert() is a O(N) operation, so below implemetation has O(N^2) time complexity.
```
public class Solution {
    public IList<int> AddToArrayForm(int[] A, int K) {

        char[] B = K.ToString().ToArray();

        int carry = 0, i1 = A.Length - 1, i2 = B.Length - 1;
        List<int> res = new List<int>();
        while(i1 >= 0 || i2 >= 0 || carry > 0)
        {
            int val1 = i1 >= 0? A[i1] : 0;
            int val2 = i2 >= 0? B[i2] - '0' : 0;
            int sum = val1 + val2 + carry;
            carry = sum / 10;
            res.Insert(0, sum % 10);
            i1--;
            i2--;
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

We can also use LinkedList to build the result. Unlike List<T> whose underlying data structure is Array, LinkedList<T> underlying data structure is a double linked list. LinkedList.AddFirst() is a O(1) operation and we can use it to build the result from LSD to MSD. Below solution will have O(N) time complexity.
```
public class Solution {
    public IList<int> AddToArrayForm(int[] A, int K) {

        char[] B = K.ToString().ToArray();

        int carry = 0, i1 = A.Length - 1, i2 = B.Length - 1;
        LinkedList<int> res = new LinkedList<int>();
        while(i1 >= 0 || i2 >= 0 || carry > 0)
        {
            int val1 = i1 >= 0? A[i1] : 0;
            int val2 = i2 >= 0? B[i2] - '0' : 0;
            int sum = val1 + val2 + carry;
            carry = sum / 10;
            res.AddFirst(sum % 10);
            i1--;
            i2--;
        }

        return new List<int>(res);
    }
}
```

