# Intuition
We will be using ArrayList and using the number ```k``` as the carry we'll add the following.
We will begin from ```nums.length-1``` that is its last element and add ```k``` to each and store remainder in the ArrayList.
We'll keep updating and removing the last digit of ```k```.
After travelsing array if ```k>0``` then we add remaining digits of ```k```.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
```
Example: `num` = [2,1,5], `k` = 806
At index 2 num = [2, 1, 811] 
So, `k` = 81 and `num` = [2, 1, 1]

At index 1 num = [2, 82, 1]
So, `k` = 8 and `num` = [2, 2, 1]

At index 0 num = [10, 2, 1]
So, `k` = 1 and `num` = [0, 2, 1]

Now `k` > 0
So, we add at the beginning of num
`num` = [1, 0, 2, 1]
```
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        //new ArrayList  to store and return 
        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();

        for(int i=num.length-1; i>=0; i--){
