# Intuition
- It's same problem as the following leetcode problems 
    1. Add Two Numbers
    2. Add Binary(yesterday POTD)

# Approach
- The approach is always same we have to make sure the usage of carry while adding the numbers and little bit of maths.
- So we always gonna take sum variable to calculate the sum of *nth* digit place and we will use % operator for the last digit of sum and / operator for calculating the modulus.
- Note that modulus if taken for the next carry each time if the mod becomes zero then there is no carry for the next digit sum.
- And regarding the last if statement suppose we have a digit lets say [Our given array is [9,9,9] and k = 1]. In this example the carry does always exists and its even exceeding the original space by 1. So to avoid this edge case we use the if statement outside the loop to accumulate all the digits in our given array.
- Reverse the answer array and return it. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
- O(n)
- Space complexity:
- O(n+k)
*Exaplanation* : 
O(k) for the digit to store in the vector form
O(n)/O(n+1)[which is the edge case in our question].
SO O(n)/O(n+1) ~ O(n)


If u liked the solution the upvote would be appreciated :)

